# Bookmarks System

Bookmarks allow users to save important learning moments.

They act as a knowledge retrieval layer.

---

# Product Vision

Bookmarks must:

- capture important content instantly
- support cross-module saving
- enable fast retrieval
- improve revision efficiency

---

# Architecture

Presentation Layer

↓

BookmarksController (Riverpod)

↓

BookmarksState

↓

BookmarksRepository

↓

Local DB + Sync Service

---

# State Management

BookmarksState includes:

- loading
- synced
- updated
- error

Core Data:

- bookmarkedItems
- tags
- categories
- sourceType
- timestamps

---

# Bookmark Types

- Lesson Bookmark
- AI Response Bookmark
- Quiz Question Bookmark
- Exam Question Bookmark
- Flashcard Bookmark

---

# Tagging System

Users can:

- add tags
- group bookmarks
- filter by category

AI may auto-suggest tags.

---

# Navigation Rules

Bookmarks must be accessible from:

- Dashboard
- Lesson Player
- AI Tutor
- Quiz Engine
- Profile

---

# Offline Behaviour

- full offline access
- sync when online
- conflict resolution on merge

---

# API Contracts

GET /bookmarks

POST /bookmarks/add

DELETE /bookmarks/remove

POST /bookmarks/sync

---

# Analytics Events

bookmark_add

bookmark_remove

bookmark_open

bookmark_filter_used

---

# UI Composition Rules

Bookmarks UI must include:

- list view
- filtering system
- tag chips
- source indicators
- quick search

---

# UX Rules

- bookmarking must be instant
- no confirmation dialogs
- allow undo removal

---

# Error Handling

- retry sync automatically
- preserve local changes

---

# Performance

- instant save (<100ms local)
- lazy load lists

---

# Accessibility

Must support:

- keyboard navigation
- screen reader labeling
- clear grouping of items

---

# Testing Requirements

Unit Tests:

Bookmark creation logic

Sync system

Tagging logic

Widget Tests:

Bookmark list UI

Tag filters

Integration Tests:

Cross-feature bookmarking

Offline sync flow

---

# Cursor Instructions

When generating bookmarks:

- always make bookmarking instant
- always support cross-module saving
- always implement tagging system
- never block UI for sync